##increase size of disk
create a new HD in Virtual Box
mount ubuntu DVD
boot with ubuntu live from DVD
once booted open gparted
sudo dd if=/dev/sda of=/dev/sdb
allocate space on gparted new disk
refresh disk gparted
note the size of the swap partion and delete it together with the extended partition 
resize the os partition leaving anough space for the swap partition
recreate swap partion (create as extended pertion click unallocated again as extended file system linux-swap)
apply all operations
shut down vm
empty disk drive
remove old disk
